Newer P2Y12 ADP Inhibitors. A high rate of recurrent atherothrombotic events despite the administration of dual-antiplatelet therapy with aspirin and clopidogrel has

sparked great interest in finding more potent inhibitors of the P2Y12 ADP receptor.
Prasugrel is an irreversible P2Y12 ADP receptor antagonist that was recently approved by the US Food and Drug Administration. Several studies have shown that prasugrel achieves much higher (nearly double) levels of platelet inhi-

